{"key":"processedPost-5347051","value":{"id":5347051,"first":5346372,"last":5348144,"when":1141097713,"utime":"02/28/06 05:35 AM","content":"There should be NO standing water in the perlite.  Any standing water will LOWER the humidity.  Dump it out and get rid of that alcohol!  Perlite contains no nutrients and won't contaminate.  Simply put the perlite in a collander and run water through it.  Drain and dump into the terrarium.   Four days is also too soon to see any difference.  Wait two weeks, and if the alcohol fumes didn't kill your mycelium, you should see some pinning.<br />RR","title":"Re: Casing layer not colonizing","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}